subSection.paragraph:
There are very few known freshwater species in Sweden compared to other temperate regions. Limiting the assessment to the most studied countries, 90 species are known from Germany (Remane, 1936 ;
Schwank, 1990
), 98 species from Poland (
Kisielewski, 1998
), 91 species from Russia (
Tretjakova, 1991
) and 58 species from United Kingdom (
Martin, 1990
). From this it is predicted that many more species should be present in Sweden .

